const rawHTML = `
<div class="c">

<!-- Hero -->
<div class="hero">
  <div class="hero-k">How-To &middot; Travel &middot; Peptide Storage</div>
  <h1>How to Travel with Peptides: TSA Rules, Storage Tips, and Packing Guide</h1>
  <p class="sub">Everything you need to know about flying domestically, crossing international borders, maintaining cold chain, and keeping your peptide supply intact from departure to destination.</p>
  <div class="pills">
    <span class="pill">TSA &middot; Domestic Flights</span>
    <span class="pill">International Customs</span>
    <span class="pill">Cold Chain &middot; Storage</span>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Stats -->
<div class="sr">
  <div class="sb"><div class="v c1">36-46&deg;F</div><div class="l">Safe Storage<br>Temperature</div></div>
  <div class="sb"><div class="v c2">25%</div><div class="l">Extra Supply<br>Recommended</div></div>
  <div class="sb"><div class="v c3">24-48h</div><div class="l">Phase Change<br>Cooling Duration</div></div>
  <div class="sb"><div class="v c4">3 Weeks</div><div class="l">Minimum Prep<br>Before Travel</div></div>
</div>

<p>Traveling with <a href="/articles/what-are-peptides-beginners-guide">peptides</a> forces you to solve problems that don't exist with traditional medications. These biological compounds are temperature-sensitive, legally ambiguous in some regions, and unfamiliar to most security officers.</p>

<p>A ruined peptide supply means wasted money and interrupted treatment protocols. The good news: thousands of people fly with peptides every week without incident. They just plan ahead.</p>

<div class="d">
  <div class="s">What This Guide Covers</div>
  <p>TSA rules for domestic flights, international customs requirements, cold chain maintenance, packing strategies, hotel storage solutions, required documentation, and common mistakes that ruin peptide supplies mid-trip.</p>
</div>

<!-- ========== TSA RULES ========== -->
<hr class="sep">
<h2>TSA and Domestic Air Travel Rules</h2>

<p>The TSA allows peptides in both carry-on and checked luggage. Peptides classify as medications, which exempts them from standard liquid restrictions when you declare them properly.</p>

<p>Tell TSA officers about your peptides before screening begins. Present them in a separate clear bag along with any cooling equipment.</p>

<div class="cd cb">
  <div class="tg">Key Rule</div>
  <h3>Always Declare Before Screening</h3>
  <p style="font-size:14px;margin-bottom:0;">Inform the TSA officer that you are carrying medical peptides and cooling equipment <strong>before</strong> they begin scanning your bag. This prevents delays, demonstrates compliance, and gives you a chance to explain what the vials contain. Original pharmacy labels reduce questioning significantly.</p>
</div>

<table class="tbl">
  <thead><tr><th>Item Type</th><th>TSA Status</th><th>Requirements</th></tr></thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td>Lyophilized peptide vials</td><td class="g">Allowed</td><td>No declaration needed</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Reconstituted peptides</td><td class="g">Allowed</td><td>Must declare as medication</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Ice packs (frozen solid)</td><td class="g">Permitted</td><td>Any size for medications</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Gel cooling packs</td><td class="y">Permitted</td><td>Must be frozen at checkpoint</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Insulin travel cases</td><td class="g">Recommended</td><td>Medical exemption applies</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

<p>Officers may inspect your cooling containers separately. They cannot require you to open sealed medication vials, but they may test the exterior for explosive residue. Carry printed TSA medication guidelines to clarify any confusion at the checkpoint.</p>

<p>Never pack peptides in checked luggage if you can avoid it. Cargo holds swing between extreme temperatures that destroy peptide stability. The cabin keeps conditions more controlled and keeps your supply within reach.</p>

<div class="d-a">
  <div class="s">Pre-Check Tip</div>
  <p>TSA PreCheck members still need to declare peptides, but they get shorter wait times. The medical liquid exemption applies regardless of your security program enrollment.</p>
</div>

<!-- ========== INTERNATIONAL ========== -->
<hr class="sep">
<h2>International Travel Considerations</h2>

<p>International peptide transport gets complicated fast. Regulations vary wildly between countries, and what's perfectly legal at home may trigger customs violations abroad.</p>

<p>Some nations require prescriptions for all peptide forms. Others restrict certain compounds entirely, regardless of medical need.</p>

